description: Returns the time series of values for a requested list of frame metrics from a time period.

parameters.name: frameMetrics
parameters.description: The details of the metrics that are used to request a time series of values. The metric includes the name of the frame, the aggregation type to calculate the metric value for the frame, and the thread states to use to get the count for the metric value of the frame. (dict) --- The frame name, metric type, and thread states. These are used to derive the value of the metric for the frame. Name of the method common across the multiple occurrences of a frame in an application profile. List of application runtime thread states used to get the counts for a frame a derive a metric value. (string) --- A type of aggregation that specifies how a metric for a frame is analyzed. The supported value AggregatedRelativeTotalTime is an aggregation of the metric value for one frame that is calculated across the occurrences of all frames in a profile.

nested_params.name: frameName
nested_params.description: Name of the method common across the multiple occurrences of a frame in an application profile.

nested_params.name: threadStates
nested_params.description: List of application runtime thread states used to get the counts for a frame a derive a metric value.

nested_params.name: type
nested_params.description: A type of aggregation that specifies how a metric for a frame is analyzed. The supported value AggregatedRelativeTotalTime is an aggregation of the metric value for one frame that is calculated across the occurrences of all frames in a profile.

parameters.name: profilingGroupName
parameters.description: The name of the profiling group associated with the the frame metrics used to return the time series values.

parameters.name: targetResolution
parameters.description: The requested resolution of time steps for the returned time series of values. If the requested target resolution is not available due to data not being retained we provide a best effort result by falling back to the most granular available resolution after the target resolution. There are 3 valid values. P1D -- 1 day PT1H -- 1 hour PT5M -- 5 minutes.

nested_items.name: endTime
nested_items.description: The end time of the time period for the returned time series values. This is specified using the ISO 8601 format. For example, 2020-06-01T13:15:02.001Z represents 1 millisecond past June 1, 2020 1:15:02 PM UTC.

nested_items.name: endTimes
nested_items.description: List of instances, or time steps, in the time series. For example, if the period is one day ( PT24H)), and the resolution is five minutes ( PT5M), then there are 288 endTimes in the list that are each five minutes appart.

nested_items.name: value
nested_items.description: A Timestamp. This is specified using the ISO 8601 format. For example, 2020-06-01T13:15:02.001Z represents 1 millisecond past June 1, 2020 1:15:02 PM UTC.
